Care to use `update_fields=tuple(defaults)`? Also, how about this for the else branch in line 104:
```python
if states.state(state) < states.state(obj.state):
    keep = Task.merge_rules[states.RECEIVED]
else:
    keep = {}
for k, v in defaults.items():
    if k not in keep:
        setattr(obj, k, v)
obj.save(update_fields=tuple(defaults.keys()))
```

Rather than setting self.stream each time maybe do something like this:

```python
    @property
    def stream(self):
        if self._use_stderr:
            return sys.stderr
        return sys.stdout
```

